About Data

The data collected from a direct marketing campaign by a Portuguese bank. The goal of the campaign was to persuade clients to subscribe to a term deposit. The dataset includes various attributes related to the clients, such as demographic information, job status, and previous interactions with the bank, along with details about the marketing campaign itself, including call duration, contact method, and campaign outcomes. The target variable is whether the client subscribed to the term deposit, making this dataset suitable for classification tasks, particularly in predicting customer behavior.

# Data Cleaning
def CleanFunc(data):
    # Impute missing values (mean/mode imputation)
    for column in data.columns:
        if data[column].dtype == 'object':
            # Use mode for categorical columns
            data[column].fillna(data[column].mode()[0], inplace=True)
        else:
            #  mean for numerical columns
            data[column].fillna(data[column].mean(), inplace=True)
    print(f"Data after imputing missing values: {data.shape}")
    
    # One-hot encoding for categorical variables
    categorical_cols = data.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
    data = pd.get_dummies(data, columns=categorical_cols, drop_first=True)
    
    return data

def Ftrslct(data):
    X = data.drop(columns=['deposit_yes'])
    y = data['deposit_yes']

    # Initialize StandardScaler
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    
    # Scale the features
    X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

    # Initialize RandomForestClassifier 
    model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)

    # Use RFE to select the top features
    rfe = RFE(estimator=model, n_features_to_select=12)
    fit = rfe.fit(X_scaled, y) 
    
    # Get the selected features
    selected_columns = X.columns[fit.support_]
    print(f'Selected Features: {selected_columns.tolist()}')

    selected_df = X[selected_columns]

    # Fit the RandomForestClassifier on the selected features
    model.fit(X_scaled[:, fit.support_], y)

    # Get the feature importances for the selected features
    selected_importances = model.feature_importances_

    selected_feature_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({
        'Feature': selected_columns,
        'Importance': selected_importances
    })

    selected_feature_importance_df = selected_feature_importance_df.sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)

    # Plot the feature importances
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='Importance', y='Feature', data=selected_feature_importance_df, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('Feature Importance of Selected Features')
    plt.xlabel('Importance Score')
    plt.ylabel('Selected Features')
    plt.show()
    
    # Calculate the correlation matrix of the selected features
    correlation_matrix = selected_df.corr()

    # Plot heatmap of the correlation matrix
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap='coolwarm', cbar=True)
    plt.title('Heatmap of Selected Features Correlation')
    plt.show()

    return selected_df

def PCAViz(data):
    pca = PCA(n_components=2)
    pca_data = pca.fit_transform(data)

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.scatter(pca_data[:, 0], pca_data[:, 1], c='blue', edgecolor='k')
    plt.title('PCA of Selected Features')
    plt.xlabel('PCA 1')
    plt.ylabel('PCA2 2')
    plt.show()
    
    os.environ["LOKY_MAX_CPU_COUNT"] = "4"  # suppose 4 cores CPU

    # t-SNE 2D projection
    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42)
    tsne_result = tsne.fit_transform(data)

    # Plotting t-SNE result as well
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.scatter(tsne_result[:, 0], tsne_result[:, 1], c='red', cmap='plasma')
    plt.title('t-SNE 2D Projection')
    plt.xlabel('t-SNE1')
    plt.ylabel('t-SNE2')
    plt.show()

    return pca_data, tsne_result

def find_optimal_k(data):
    X = data.drop(columns=['deposit_yes'])  # Exclude target variable

    inertia = []
    K = range(1, 11)  # Test for k from 1 to 10

    for k in K:
        kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42)
        kmeans.fit(X)
        inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)

    # Plot the Elbow Curve
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.plot(K, inertia, 'bo-')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters (k)')
    plt.ylabel('Inertia')
    plt.title('Elbow Method for Optimal k')
    plt.show()

def clusterfunction(data, n_clusters=2):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, random_state=42)
    clusters = kmeans.fit_predict(data)
    
    return clusters, kmeans

def Vizfunc(pca_data, clusters):
    # PCA visualization
    pca = PCA(n_components=2)
    pca_result = pca.fit_transform(data)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    plt.scatter(pca_result[:, 0], pca_result[:, 1], c=clusters, cmap='viridis')
    plt.title('Cluster Visualization using PCA')
    plt.xlabel('PCA1')
    plt.ylabel('PCA2')
    plt.show()

    # t-SNE visualization
    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42)
    tsne_result = tsne.fit_transform(data)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    plt.scatter(tsne_result[:, 0], tsne_result[:, 1], c=clusters, cmap='plasma')
    plt.title('Cluster Visualization using t-SNE')
    plt.xlabel('t-SNE1')
    plt.ylabel('t-SNE2')
    plt.show()

    # Polar plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    for cluster in np.unique(clusters):
        cluster_data = pca_result[clusters == cluster]
        plt.polar(cluster_data[:, 0], cluster_data[:, 1], marker='o', linestyle='', label=f'Cluster {cluster}')
    plt.title('Polar Plot of Clusters')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

    # Radius plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.scatter(pca_result[:, 0], np.zeros_like(pca_result[:, 0]), c=clusters, cmap='viridis')
    plt.title('Radius Plot of Clusters')
    plt.xlabel('PCA1')
    plt.show()

    # Bar chart of cluster sizes
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    cluster_counts = pd.Series(clusters).value_counts()
    cluster_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='green')
    plt.title('Cluster Sizes (Bar Chart)')
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.show()

def centroidfunction(kmeans, data):
    centroids = kmeans.cluster_centers_
    print("Centroids of each cluster:")
    for i, centroid in enumerate(centroids):
        print(f"Centroid of Cluster {i}: {centroid}")

def rand_index(data_copy, clusters):
    actual_classes = data_copy['deposit_yes']
    rand_score = adjusted_rand_score(actual_classes, clusters)
    print(f'Adjusted Rand Index: {rand_score}')

def KProto_clusters_and_visualize():

    data = Load_data()
    
    data_encoded = pd.get_dummies(data, drop_first=True)

    X = data_encoded.drop(columns=['deposit_yes'])  # label
    y_true = data['deposit'].map({'yes': 1, 'no': 0}).values  
    
    # K-Prototypes clustering
    kproto = KPrototypes(n_clusters=2, init='Cao', random_state=42)
    clusters_kproto = kproto.fit_predict(X, categorical=[1, 2, 3]) 

    # Performance metrics
    ari_kproto = adjusted_rand_score(y_true, clusters_kproto)
    nmi_kproto = normalized_mutual_info_score(y_true, clusters_kproto)

    print(f"K-Prototypes ARI: {ari_kproto}")
    print(f"K-Prototypes NMI: {nmi_kproto}")

    # Visualization of clusters
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.countplot(x=clusters_kproto, hue=y_true)
    plt.title('K-Prototypes Clustering Results')
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='True Label', loc='upper right', labels=['No', 'Yes'])
    plt.show()

    #  PCA Visualization
    pca = PCA(n_components=2)
    X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x=X_pca[:, 0], y=X_pca[:, 1], hue=clusters_kproto, palette='viridis', alpha=0.6)
    plt.title('PCA Visualization of Clusters')
    plt.xlabel('PCA Component 1')
    plt.ylabel('PCA Component 2')
    plt.legend(title='Cluster')
    plt.show()

    #  t-SNE Visualization
    tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42)
    X_tsne = tsne.fit_transform(X)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x=X_tsne[:, 0], y=X_tsne[:, 1], hue=clusters_kproto, palette='viridis', alpha=0.6)
    plt.title('t-SNE Visualization of Clusters')
    plt.xlabel('t-SNE Component 1')
    plt.ylabel('t-SNE Component 2')
    plt.legend(title='Cluster')
    plt.show()

    #  Polar Chart
    counts = np.bincount(clusters_kproto)
    theta = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, len(counts), endpoint=False).tolist()
    counts = np.concatenate((counts, [counts[0]]))  
    theta += theta[:1]

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    ax = plt.subplot(111, polar=True)
    ax.fill(theta, counts, color='blue', alpha=0.25)
    ax.plot(theta, counts, color='blue')
    plt.title('K-Prototypes Clustering Polar Chart')
    plt.xticks(theta[:-1], [f'Cluster {i}' for i in range(len(counts)-1)])
    plt.show()

    #  Radius Chart
    labels = [f'Cluster {i}' for i in range(len(counts))]
    angles = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, len(labels), endpoint=False).tolist()
    counts = np.concatenate((counts, [counts[0]])) 
    angles += angles[:1]

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    plt.subplot(projection='polar')
    plt.bar(angles[:-1], counts[:-1], width=0.3, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('K-Prototypes Clustering Radius Chart')
    plt.xticks(angles[:-1], labels)
    plt.show()
